<h1>Problem 453 - 2011 USA TST, P9 of 9</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Determine whether or not there exist two different sets \(A,B\), each consisting of at most \(2011^2\) positive integers, such that every \(x\) with \(0 < x < 1\) satisfies the following inequality:
\[\left| \sum_{a \in A} x^a - \sum_{b \in B} x^b \right| < (1-x)^{2011}.\]</p>
